                p.left.mg-bottom2
                    | With his recent photography and light works Joosten explores a darker expanse where
                    | the light reflects from within.
                    br
                    | After his move from Japan to Germany in 2013 he started to experiment with black &
                    | white paper cut-outs and cast resin shapes placed into reliefs, projecting light from
                    | behind the paper and rain shapes.
                    br
                    | The photographic works were created by projecting a white LED light from behind the
                    | paper cut-out planes, while capturing the image with a moving camera.
                    | The light boxes consist of a black front panel hung on the wall, in which a negative
                    | silhouette has been cut out by a digital laser cutter.
                    br
                    | Behind this front panel, a semi-transparent plate is mounted. A white LED light is installed
                    | behind the panels into a black frame so that the light only shines through the cut-out
                    | openings of the front layer. The light source is connected to a small microcontroller that
                    | will move the intensity of the light as if it slowly breaths in and out, as a light source that
                    | slowly appear and dissolves.
                p.centre.italic.mg-bottom
                    | "Life is the light that shines in the darkness!"
                    br
                    | (Hayao Miyazaki, Nausicaä of the valley of the wind, Vol.7-2 The Crypt)

                p.left.mg-bottom5.
                    Creating an infinite black space in which all life appearances begins and end.
                    A silent empty void in which sinuous light whisperings emerge, slowly appearing
                    and dissolving on the brink of existence. The light breathing, in and out. A caress,
                    a sensual dance, embracing the night. A signature coming to life, a scripture fading
                    away.

                p.left.mg-bottom2
                    | Like the last moment before falling asleep, when we have laid down our clothes, our
                    | various roles and identities, we dissolve into absolute darkness. Or reversely, as the first
                    | instant in which we seem to reappear right before awakening.
                    | An infinite empty blackness in which all life appearances begin and end, the background
                    | of our being.
                p.centre.italic.mg-bottom
                    | “One does not become enlightened by imagining figures of light, but by making the darkness conscious. "
                    br
                    | (C.G. Jung “The Philosophical Tree” (1945) In Collected Works13: Alchemical Studies)

